    "body": "Seen in Windows ci. `NVIM_TEST_INTEG` not set so I don't think this is a network issue. Maybe slow filesystem?\n\n```\nSKIPPED  ...ld/Xtest_xdg_plugin/test/functional/plugin/pack_spec.lua @ 851: vim.pack add() can install from the Internet\nNVIM_TEST_INTEG not set: skipping network integration test\nFAILED   1 test, listed below:\nFAILED   ...ld/Xtest_xdg_plugin/test/functional/plugin/pack_spec.lua @ 882: vim.pack add() startup works in init.lua\n...ld/Xtest_xdg_plugin/test/functional/plugin/pack_spec.lua:882: retry() attempts: 67\nExpected values to be equal.\nExpected:\ntrue\nActual:\nvim.NIL\nstack traceback:\n\ttest/testutil.lua:88: in function 'retry'\n\t...ld/Xtest_xdg_plugin/test/functional/plugin/pack_spec.lua:882: in function 'assert_works'\n\t...ld/Xtest_xdg_plugin/test/functional/plugin/pack_spec.lua:895: in function <...ld/Xtest_xdg_plugin/test/functional/plugin/pack_spec.lua:892>\n```",
