    "comment_data": [
        {
            "author_association": "MEMBER",
            "body": "> Seen in Windows ci. `NVIM_TEST_INTEG` not set so I don't think this is a network issue. Maybe slow filesystem?\n\nIt is not the test that uses Internet connection, that is skipped.\n\nIt is a basically a test that `vim.pack.add()` is able to work during startup. [Here are the lines](https://github.com/neovim/neovim/blob/5b0ad4a0607498616b984c63ae1a6903cb835c66/test/functional/plugin/pack_spec.lua#L881-L884). I am not quite sure what is the reason here, but my guess is: if it works but is just unreliable, then increasing timeout is the only feasible solution. Like from 2000 to 5000. As it uses `t.retry`, it should not have negative impact on fast platforms.\n\nDoes that sound reasonable?",
